column2: Warm day- air temp 73.4 (1:30pm) water temp 77F at secchi test site
very hot 94F- rained hard previous morning- water temp 81F- good fishing
lots of rain 2 days previous- lake has green slime along shore
Sunny and warm 70s- heavy green slime along shore- some green all over lake
sunny warm- 77F- some green slime on shore
green slime near shore and green particles near lake
windy and warm- water clarity OK- no green
Cold night- previos- 40F- green slime in morning- water temp 63.1F
Wind NW 5-10 mph.  Sunny- few clouds.  Bob Greene helped.
Bits of algae present.  Sunny and windy.  82 F air temp.
Sunny and windy.  Bits of algae present- but very few.  69.4 F air temp.
Windy- sunny- air temp 79.7 F.  No algae today - bad yesterday.  Bob Greene helped.
Wind less than 5 mph.  Sunny.  Some algae present.
Nice day.  Some algae suspended in the water.
Chunks of algae floating on and below the suface.  First noticed 5/23.  Looks bad
Tiny algae particlel suspended throughout the lake (tiny grass-like pieces) suspended in the water.
Lots of green grass-like pieces suspended in the water.  Skum floating on top.
Sunny- windy- suspended algae throughout the lake.  Not as bad as previous week.
Sunny- little wind- slimy green along south shore- suspended algae everywhere in lake.  Loons gone.  A few boaters out.

Temp. 59 degrees F- sunny and clear. Calm winds (had been calm for 2-3 days over Labor Day weekend.  Thick algal scum on the lake and higher than normal amount of suspended algae in the water.  Without wind to move it around- the scum was all along the south and west shores.
Sunny.  Temp 70 degrees.  Moderately windy- 10 mpg out of the east.  Lake smelled rotten.
Overcast day- but warm.  Slight breeze.  Water clarity great.  NO ALGAE VISIBLE. Loon on the nest.  Pair of swans sighted.  Eagle flying over and fishing.
Sunny 37 degrees F- winds NE 10 mph
Clear sky- slight breeze 5-10 mph. Water looks good - no algae.
Breezy and sunny. 10 to 15 mph. Water looks good - no algae. Clearst in a year.  Little rain this year.
Sunny and breezy- 10 to 15 mph. Water looks good. No algae (some floating stuff near shore.)  Four plus inches of rain earlier in the week.
Sunny- calm- warm.  Water still looks good- but some grass-like peices in suspension.
Cold. 50s and snowy.  Ice out April 28.
Rain 2 days prior to testing.  Temps in low 70s.
Warm. 80s days and cool evenings all week.

Sunny- 75 degrees- calm waters but a violent storm the night before with 60-70 mph winds from NW. Lake was filled with green chunks of floating algae-like matter. Winds came up this morning and was lake was clean by noon.
60 degrees- few drops of rain and overcast. Slight breeze from north.
Sunny and winds from the north. Sunny and winds from the north
Sunny and light breeze from North at 10 mph
Sunny- 70 degrees.  Slight breeze out of North.  Loons are back.
Sunny and hot.  85 degrees F. SW winds 10-15 mph
Sunny and calm.  Some specks of algae and some little pieces of algae floating.
Little breezy- some spotty algae present. Cloudy.  Temperature 70 degrees.
Sunny- 70 degrees- slight breeze.  Water looks good.
Hazy sun- 70 degrees- slight breeze- water looks clean
Partly cloudy and 75 degrees- water looks good - no algae- but quite stained.
Partly sunny and 77 degrees.  Breezy days- cool nights.  Water looks good after wind blows crud (seeds and tree droppings)
Sunny and 71 degrees- breezy. Water quality is good- no algae.
Overcast 65 degrees- Slight breeze.  Loons on artificial nesting platform. Water looks pretty good.
Partly sunny- 66 degrees- Mild breeze.  Loons on ANP.  Water looks good
Sunny- 68 degrees- breezy- water looks great
Partly sunny- 72 degrees- breezy- water looks perfect
Sunny- mild breeze- water is beautiful
Sunny- 82 degrees- slight breeze- beautiful water- loons hanging around ANP

Sunny with a light breeze. Water full of green specs and some small pieces of algae in the bay.  One of our guests reported seeing 3 trumpeter swans.  Seems a little early- but I think she knows what they look like.
Sunny- 45 degrees- no wind- some flecks of algae in the water. Sunny- 45 degrees- no wind- some flecks of algae in the water.
Sunny-  less than 5 mph wind NNW- 70 degrees.  Cottonwood seeds and pollen on lake.
Partly sunny- 66 degrees- wind NE 10 mph. Loons on ANP. Water nice.
Sunny- windy- 76 degrees. Water is nice. Loons have a young one.
Temp 83 degrees- windy- cloudy. Lake very nice STILL. Baby loon still alive and thriving. 83 degrees- calm winds- cloudy.
60 degrees- sunny- breezy.  Water very nice.  No algae.
Partly sunny- breezy with large clouds. Overcast when measurements taken.  Heavy rain last night-
Sunny with scattered clouds.  Slight breeze.  Loons swimming nearby.  Visible particles suspended in the water.
Sunny day with scattered clouds.  Hot and humid.  Lake had ripples from the breeze.
Partly sunny- partly cloudy.  Lake rippling from the breeze.
Rained last night.  Stiff breeze.  Sunny with clouds.  Water rippling.  Pleasant temperature in the 70?s.
Partly sunny- partly cloudy.  Very breezy.  Cool - high 60?s - low 70?s.  Water rippling from the breeze.  Loon on the lake.
Sunny during observation with clouds.  Water rippling with light breeze.  Warm and pleasant.
Sunny with clouds. No Breeze.  The water is very still and calm.  It is warm and humid.
Very breezy- water ripples- sunny- mid 60?s.  Other boats on the water.
Warm mid 70?s.  Sunny with beautiful clear sky.  Breezy.  Water looks as if it has suspended particles floating.  There are campers in the campground and other boats on the lake.
Clear sunny day.  Breezy with rippling water.  Crisp and cool autumn day. Visible algae floating in the water.  Algae forming surface layer near lake shore.
